Usage: gmake [options] [target] ...
Options:
  -b, -m            Ignored for compatibility
  -B, --always-make  Unconditionally make all targets
  -d                Print lots of debugging information
  --debug[=FLAGS]   Print various types of debugging information
  -e, --environment-overrides
                    Environment variables override makefiles
  -f FILE           Read FILE as a makefile
  -h, --help        Print this message and exit
  -i, --ignore-errors
                    Ignore errors from recipes
  -I DIR            Search DIR for included makefiles
  -j [N]            Allow N jobs at once (default 1)
  -k, --keep-going  Keep going when some targets can't be made
  -l [N]            Don't start multiple jobs if load > N
  -n, --just-print  Print recipes without executing
  -o FILE           Consider FILE to be very old
  -p, --print-data-base
                    Print make's internal database
  -q, --question    Run no recipe; exit 0 if up to date
  -r, --no-builtin-rules
                    Disable built-in implicit rules
  -R, --no-builtin-variables
                    Disable built-in variable settings
  -s, --silent      Silent operation
  -S, --no-keep-going
                    Turns off -k
  -t, --touch       Touch targets instead of remaking them
  -v, --version     Print version and exit
  -w, --print-directory
                    Print the current directory
  -C DIR            Change to DIR before doing anything
  -W FILE           Consider FILE to be infinitely new
  --warn-undefined-variables
                    Warn when an undefined variable is expanded
